NAME
    Text::CSV_XS::TSV - Set Text::CSV_XS default options to parse TSV

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.003 of Text::CSV_XS::TSV (from Perl
    distribution Text-CSV_XS-TSV), released on 2019-12-12.

SYNOPSIS
    Use like you would use Text::CSV_XS with the object interface:

     use Text::CSV_XS::TSV;
     my $csv = Text::CSV_XS::TSV->new({binary=>1});
     # ...

DESCRIPTION
    This class is a simple subclass of Text::CSV_XS to set the default of
    these options (if unspecified), suitable for parsing TSV (tab-separated
    values) files:

    *   sep_char

        To "\t".

    *   quote_char

        To "undef".

    *   escape_char

        To "undef".

